| 2015 || August || Product || On August 5, Facebook launches live-streaming, initially restricted only to celebrities.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://techcrunch.com/2015/08/05/facescope/|title = Facebook Launches “Live” Streaming Video Feature, But Only For Celebrities|last = Constine|first = Josh|date = August 5, 2015|accessdate = October 18, 2015|publisher = ''[[w:TechCrunch|TechCrunch]]''}}</ref> Subsequently, on August 12, it announces that the feature will be made available to journalists and those with verified profiles.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://techcrunch.com/2015/08/12/facebook-live-livestreaming/|title = Facebook Confirms Live Broadcasting Will Soon Open To Journalists And Verified Profiles|last = Constine|first = Josh|date = August 12, 2015|accessdate = October 18, 2015|publisher = ''[[w:TechCrunch|TechCrunch]]''}}</ref>
