| 2016 || October 3 || Product || In the US, UK, Australia, and New Zealand, Facebook launches Marketplace, a way to buy and sell items through Facebook. Marketplace appears as a tab in the mobile app.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://newsroom.fb.com/news/2016/10/introducing-marketplace-buy-and-sell-with-your-local-community/ |author=Mary Ku |title=Introducing Marketplace: Buy and Sell with Your Local Community |publisher=Facebook Newsroom |accessdate=October 12, 2016 |date=October 3, 2016}}</ref> The feature has been compared to [[w:Craigslist|Craigslist]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/10/03/facebook-marketplace-2/ |author=Josh Constine |title=Facebook launches Marketplace, a friendlier Craigslist |publisher=[[w:TechCrunch|TechCrunch]] |accessdate=October 12, 2016}}</ref>
